{"books":{"2":{"id":"4816","title":"Ghosts","description":"<p>Henrik Ibsen's Ghosts was first published in 1881 and staged in 1882, and like his earlier play A Doll's House, profoundly shocked his contemporaries.  Dubbed \"a dirty deed done in public\" by one of its critics, the play focuses on (among other things) venereal disease, euthanasia, and incest.  The original title literally means \"the ones who return,\" and the play is about how we can deal with the awful legacy of the past. (Summary by Elizabeth Klett)<\/p>\n<strong>Cast:<\/strong><br><br>Mrs. Alving: <a href=\"http:\/\/librivox.org\/reader\/1259\">Elizabeth Klett<\/a><br>Oswald Alving: <a href=\"http:\/\/librivox.org\/reader\/1492\">mb<\/a><br>Pastor Manders: <a href=\"http:\/\/librivox.org\/reader\/3699\">Bruce Pirie<\/a><br>Jacob Engstrand: <a href=\"http:\/\/librivox.org\/reader\/4705\">Algy Pug<\/a><br>Regina Engstrand: <a href=\"http:\/\/librivox.org\/reader\/4174\">Availle<\/a><br>Narrator: <a href=\"http:\/\/librivox.org\/reader\/688\">J. M. Smallheer<\/a><br><br><strong>Audio edited by:<\/strong> mb<br\/>","url_text_source":"http:\/\/www.gutenberg.org\/ebooks\/8121","language":"English","copyright_year":"1881","num_sections":"6","url_rss":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/rss\/4816","url_zip_file":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/download\/ghosts_1012_librivox\/ghosts_1012_librivox_64kb_mp3.zip","url_project":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ghosts_(play)","url_librivox":"http:\/\/librivox.org\/ghosts-by-henrik-ibsen\/","url_other":null,"totaltime":"2:10:00","totaltimesecs":7800,"authors":[{"id":"477","first_name":"Henrik","last_name":"Ibsen","dob":"1828","dod":"1906"}],"url_iarchive":"http:\/\/www.archive.org\/details\/ghosts_1012_librivox","sections":[{"id":"48731","section_number":"1","title":"Act 1","listen_url":"","language":"English","playtime":"3240","file_name":null,"readers":[{"reader_id":"1259","display_name":"Elizabeth Klett"},{"reader_id":"4705","display_name":"Algy Pug"}]},{"id":"48732","section